d scale can weigh items as light as 0.1 ounces and as heavy as 11 pounds. That’s an average range for the scales we tested.","Another one of the MIRA’s helpful features is its tare button, which allows you to zero out the weight of a container so you can weigh only the contents. The tare button doubles as the power button, and unlike on other scales, it is labeled “zero” instead of “tare.”","The MIRA’s glass surface is easy to clean – food and liquid wipe right off. Also, since the weighing surface is slightly wider than the rest of the scale, there’s little chance of gunk getting in the scale’s innards. The scale has a 42-square-inch weighing area, which is more than enough room to weigh ingredients that go into average home meals.","With the MIRA Digital Kitchen Scale, you can weigh food in grams, ounces and pounds. These are the most common units of measurement found in recipes, so it should fit most of your recipes, unless you have one that calls for kilograms or fluid ounces. If you need to measure in milliliters, consider the <a href=\"/ozeri-touch-ii-review\">Ozeri Touch II</a>. You can switch the unit while the item is still on the scale. That way, you can get dual measurements during a single weigh."]},"id":"575f1c0d-b1a8-4381-8fe7-a00617b16db3","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_57612","url":"/mira-digital-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"linda-thomson","url":"/author/linda-thomson","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Linda Thomson","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"SD7AJ8PTDFstvquABQDpsH","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2013-09-25T19:13:14Z","datePublished":"2013-09-25T19:13:14Z","name":"MIRA Digital Kitchen Scale ST85","synopsis":"The MIRA Digital Kitchen Scale is a medium-size digital food scale that has a lot to recommend it.","review":{"rating":88,"verdict":"The MIRA Digital Kitchen Scale is a durable, accurate and stylish scale that